得这个行业在萎缩呢？</p><p>自上次在美国举办大型电子游戏展以来已经过去了四年。 E3 2019 标志着业界最后一次在洛杉矶举行一周的游戏和硬件发布会，今年终于再次举行，只是在新的管理下。夏季游戏节将于今天（6 月 8 日）开幕，由游戏大奖背后的团队组织，而非娱乐软件协会。东部时间下午 3 点将有一个主要的现场表演和多个关注独立游戏的后续流，以及 Xbox、Ubisoft 和 Capcom 的活动将持续到 6 月 12 日。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Summer Game Fest 的形式看起来确实很眼熟，但自上次大型夏季展会以来，行业本身已经发生了翻天覆地的变化。 Xbox Series X 和 PlayStation 5 已经上市两年多了，基于订阅的云服务实际上是可行的，独立和 AA 空间又站稳了脚跟。与此同时，房间里最大的公司一直在疯狂收购，微软和索尼收购了有才华的工作室，试图用独家游戏来填充他们的新平台。</p><p>有关完整故事，请观看下面的视频。 </p><div id="67aa1486bbb9436ebc26e59dec840975"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/cTb8Z_Us7vA?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no"></iframe></div><p><a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/sgf-2023"><em>在这里</em></a><em>了解夏季游戏节的所有新闻</em><em>！</em></p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/summer-game-fest-2023-and-the-stagnant-state-of-the-industry-163019962.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/summer-game-fest-2023-and-the-stagnant-state-of-the-industry-163019962.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 030b0baf-10da-4fa5-a3cb-3b602406894d</guid><dc:creator>杰西卡·康迪特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Thu, 08 Jun 2023 16:30:19 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686240908</ingested><modified> 2023-06-08T16:15:12+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jessica Conditt]]></category><media:content height="1208" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-11/b2e72822-1ecb-11eb-bdff-1d940f3a111a" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1208" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-11/b2e72822-1ecb-11eb-bdff-1d940f3a111a" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Aaron Souppouris / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Microsoft Series S gaming console.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Microsoft Series S (watermark)]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[How to choose the best pizza oven in 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>近年来，小型户外披萨烤箱已成为流行的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-fall-outdoor-tech-gear-150041103.html">后院</a>烹饪选择。虽然任何拥有中等大小露台的人都可以安装永久性露台，但这些多功能产品更紧凑，不用时可以轻松存放在包中。这使得这些便携式披萨烤箱非常适合户外空间有限的家庭厨师，并允许您根据需要携带它们上路。在室内安装专用比萨饼烤箱也有很多不错的选择。以下是您在购买前需要考虑的一些规格，以及一些帮助您入门和制作完美披萨的建议。</p><h2>要找什么</h2><p>在购买家用披萨烤箱时，您首先要考虑您打算制作哪种类型的披萨。大多数来自 Ooni、Solo Stove 和其他公司的便携式户外披萨烤箱都使用木材，主要设计用于轻盈通风的那不勒斯风格披萨所需的高温烹饪。我们说的是高达 900 华氏度的高温。这些装置当然可以在较冷的温度下烹饪不同的风格，但当你用满载的木材将它们敞开运行时，它们最容易使用。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>如果您购买丙烷或天然气燃烧器，您可以通过转动旋钮轻松调节温度。出于这个原因，我建议您多花 100 美元左右购买该配件。这种双燃料选项使您的比萨烤箱更加通用，并且当您不想弄乱木头或木炭时，您可以选择仍然拥有新鲜烤制的馅饼。如果您只想用煤气做饭，可以使用仅使用丙烷或天然气的型号。</p><p>另一个关键考虑因素是尺寸。大多数公司生产适合 12 英寸比萨饼的烤箱，这是一个人吃的完美尺寸。它们也非常适合举办披萨派对，因为人们可以定制自己的披萨，而无需挑选他们不喜欢的配料。如果您想制作更大的比萨饼或计划将烤箱用于其他东西（平底锅等），请考虑使用更大的版本，它不仅可以容纳小馅饼。大多数产品页面上都会列出内部尺寸——或者至少比萨饼尺寸。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-04/5d227b90-d88e-11ed-abef-0e6778381ba5" alt="2023 年最好的披萨烤箱" data-uuid="6d884542-b842-38a2-b0ce-8f51a108a27e"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">比利·斯蒂尔/Engadget 摄</div></figure><h2>成功计划</h2><p>在家制作优质披萨需要相当大的柜台或桌面空间。您需要空间来拉伸和准备比萨饼面团、布置配料并将馅饼放在果皮上。当然，有些人会喜欢在狭小的小厨房里工作，但我发现使用额外的空间来确保我不会在这个过程的各个步骤中不断地移动东西要容易得多。</p><p>将比萨饼制作站设置在离烤箱很近的地方也不会那么麻烦。作为一名面包师初学者，我经常从厨房跑到后门廊。这远非理想。当您无法近距离观察时，很难维持生火（如果使用木头或木炭）。好消息是一张露台桌可以很容易地变成一个带有大切菜板的披萨台。这也使您的烤箱离开地面，因此更容易接近。</p><p> Ooni <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Ooni Pizza Ovens;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=0de15002-ec35-49d8-b24c-3d060213cd2b&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Ooni+Pizza+Ovens&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIwZGUxNTAwMi1lYzM1LTQ5ZDgtYjI0Yy0zZDA2MDIxM2NkMmIiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9vb25pLmNvbS9jb2xsZWN0aW9ucy9tb3JlIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJlNTgyZGU0Ny04NTUxLTQzODMtYmVhNy0xMTI4OWIxNDMyZTgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAVpCSPYvpwI5lfnVJUfzhd1ZlHNXKWc0Kq5RmAT8AHRu&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fooni.com%2Fcollections%2Fmore">销售其烤箱的桌子</a>，还提供搁架和存放果皮和其他配件的地方。 Solo Stove 的 Pi 烤箱也有一个<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Solo Stove;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f5421854-3d3e-46b7-ba38-db91920c7f00&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Solo+Stove&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmNTQyMTg1NC0zZDNlLTQ2YjctYmEzOC1kYjkxOTIwYzdmMDAiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9zb2xvc3RvdmUuY29tL2VuLXVzL3AvcGktc3RhbmQiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImU1ODJkZTQ3LTg1NTEtNDM4My1iZWE3LTExMjg5YjE0MzJlOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAUKHwEUykJvcI06_XD6oAcpNoanJJR--93u-mD8kpP85&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fsolostove.com%2Fen-us%2Fp%2Fpi-stand">滚动支架</a>，旁边有小架子，下面有一个放丙烷罐的地方。当然，您可以找到其他适合您需要的桌子和支架，只要确保它们能够承受烹饪时烤箱底部可能散发的任何热量即可。大多数烤箱要么隔热良好，要么不会向桌子投射过多的热量，但您永远不能太小心。因此，不锈钢或金属表面是设置户外模型的不错选择。</p><p>这些披萨烤箱中的大多数都可以在高温下快速烹饪，尤其是当您制作那不勒斯风格的馅饼时。把你需要的一切都放在附近，这样你就可以密切关注烤箱并快速制作下一个披萨，这将减轻很多不必要的麻烦。当你的烹饪时间是两分钟或更短时，你不想冒险太远。</p><h2>户外披萨烤炉</h2><h3>一款不错的多燃料户外披萨烤箱：Ooni Karu 16</h3><p><core-commerce id="8367926575a042b3b60489c470fbb6db" data-type="product-list"></p><p>如果您想在户外比萨烤炉上全力以赴， <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdlmvMi7k25EJJDjFNPU2W_bx6VJqdXqxG1Z6YBHWKI6&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FOoni-Karu-Multi-Fuel-Outdoor-Pizza%2Fdp%2FB095CJ5KSD%2F">Ooni 的 Karu 16</a>绝对不会出错。这是该公司最大的多燃料型号，这意味着您可以选择木材、木炭或天然气（丙烷和天然气燃烧器单独出售）。 This one is equipped with a hinged glass door for keeping tabs on your progress and a digital thermometer monitors the ambient temperature inside. The larger size means you can not only cook bigger pizzas, but the Karu 16 can also accommodate pans and cast iron, so baking, roasting and searing are all possible here. It&#39;s this versatility and ease of use that makes the Karu 16 our top pick.</p><h3> A solid outdoor pizza oven: Solo Stove Pi</h3><p><core-commerce id="3ae80c749a4346a185e2f54390f6106c" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Solo Stove may be on your radar for <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/solo-stoves-fire-pit-20-removable-base-plate-ash-pan-cleanup-143100211.html">its fire pits</a> , but the company also makes a <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAARw-Do09kGbwfRdiZRKlaXkKuq5J7mbqweiatd-dPp5f&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSolo-Stove-Assembly-Cordierite-Stainless%2Fdp%2FB0B7XXXCZG%2F">solid multi-fuel pizza oven</a> . Dubbed the Pi, this unit is made out of stainless steel and is round like the company&#39;s trademark products. Solo Stove says Pi can hit cooking temperatures of 850 degrees Fahrenheit with wood and 900 degrees with a gas burner (sold separately). It explains that those figures translate to maximum stone temps of 750 and 800 degrees respectively. The Solo Stove Pi&#39;s big difference from the Karu 16 and other Ooni ovens is that it doesn&#39;t have a front door and stays open the whole time like a brick oven.</p><h3> A great smaller option: Ooni Fyra 12</h3><p><core-commerce id="4c4c3bf387d84aacb46602119cc775cc" data-type="product-list"></p><p> The <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAASFRLfAzMLiznhxBXI5Wuh0iHp4OF_3dwFo9cR_xUWyZ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FOoni-Fyra-Outdoor-Portable-Kitchen%2Fdp%2FB088385N9Z%2F">Ooni Fyra 12</a> was the first outdoor pizza oven I used and it remains one of my favorites. It&#39;s compact compared to some of the alternatives (22 pounds), so it won&#39;t take up quite as much storage space. It also runs on wood pellets instead of chunks, and once you get the fire going, you just refill the chute from the top. This means there&#39;s much less tending a fire on the Fyra than other wood-fired pizza ovens, so you can focus on making and cooking your pizzas. The Fyra does all the things other Ooni pizza ovens do well, including high-heat bakes (950 degrees) in as little as a minute.</p><h2> Indoor pizza ovens</h2><p> Let me preface this section by saying you probably already have an indoor option that you can use to make some great pizza. Whether that&#39;s the main oven in your kitchen or a multi-function countertop unit, with some affordable accessories, you can easily up your game without spending $1,000 on a dedicated appliance. For example, my <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAVcylFxGokn8E7kN4RYhg0kXpXkUgvfVEyVbjXsQ9LQt&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBreville-BOV860BSS-Countertop-Convection-Stainless%2Fdp%2FB085FTBLC6">Breville Smart Oven Air Fryer</a> has a convection pizza setting that automatically adjusts cook time based on the size, oven temperature and whether the pie is fresh or frozen. A key consideration here is size. These things are massive, about the size of a large microwave, so you likely won&#39;t want to keep them out all the time unless you have a huge kitchen.</p><h3> A versatile indoor pizza oven: Ooni Volt 12</h3><p><core-commerce id="33bf4ffb93984ec88bb89000fd3bc3b9" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Ooni made its name on outdoor pizza ovens that primarily burn wood or run on gas. For 2023, the company is taking things indoors with the <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Ooni Pizza Ovens;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=0de15002-ec35-49d8-b24c-3d060213cd2b&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Ooni+Pizza+Ovens&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIwZGUxNTAwMi1lYzM1LTQ5ZDgtYjI0Yy0zZDA2MDIxM2NkMmIiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9vb25pLmNvbS9wcm9kdWN0cy9vb25pLXZvbHQiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImU1ODJkZTQ3LTg1NTEtNDM4My1iZWE3LTExMjg5YjE0MzJlOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAbs6K5UOSm8E-W_bMajznrC6hE6gSrwegRQG3GoG3gqs&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fooni.com%2Fproducts%2Fooni-volt">Volt 12</a> . <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/oonis-volt-12-is-the-companys-first-indoor-pizza-oven-173011466.html">Ooni&#39;s first electric oven</a> can also be used outside thanks to weather resistant construction, but this behemoth brings the company&#39;s design and efficiency to your kitchen for the first time. Capable of temperatures up to 850 degrees Fahrenheit in as little as 20 minutes, the Volt 12 can fire up Neapolitan style pies in 90 seconds. Controls on the front give you the ability to adjust both the top and bottom heating elements. There are also cooking presets and a Boost function to quickly get the stone back to temp between pizzas. The 13-inch stone inside is square, so you can slide in pans for Detroit recipes or other baked goods.</p><h3> A solid indoor pizza oven: Breville Pizzaiolo</h3><p><core-commerce id="c6f69080a1ba415c81d05f070daaf78e" data-type="product-list"></p><p> If you&#39;re set on buying a dedicated pizza oven, the <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9CcmV2aWxsZS1QaXp6YWlvbG8tQlBaODIwQlNTLUJydXNoZWQtU3RhaW5sZXNzL2RwL0IwOFI4WVpSMzI_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tc3AtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImU1ODJkZTQ3LTg1NTEtNDM4My1iZWE3LTExMjg5YjE0MzJlOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAZpOAEufnbwWCGDzjVUYurIRPrRyq2rE2abyRwwaeYbL&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBreville-Pizzaiolo-BPZ820BSS-Brushed-Stainless%2Fdp%2FB08R8YZR32">Breville Pizzaiolo</a> is another great option, but it&#39;s just as pricey as the Volt 12. The Pizzaiolo cooks 12-inch pies as well, but the stone on this unit is perfectly sized for them and there&#39;s a metal heat reflector panel inside that will also keep you from overshooting the cooking surface. This means you won&#39;t be sliding larger rectangle pans in here like you can with the electric Ooni. Round pans fit just fine and some smaller square ones likely will too.</p><p> In terms of cooking ability, Breville offers presets for “Wood Fired,” New York, Pan, Thin &amp; Crispy and Frozen pizzas with the added option to run the oven full blast at 750 degrees Fahrenheit. A second dial allows you to adjust the top heating element depending on how dark you want your pizza. Like it does on other Breville appliances, Element IQ tech adjusts the heating elements based on the selected style, creating the ideal environment for each one. For advanced users, the company offers a manual mode that turns the timer dial into a control for the bottom deck while the style preset selector manages the top. Breville includes a magnetic overlay for the front panel to show you temperatures for the converted controls. The instruction manual also gives you recommendations for where to begin with manual mode for the aforementioned styles.</p><h3> The best pizza accessories for the oven you already have</h3><p> If you want to make good homemade pizza that rivals that of your favorite pizzeria (and without spending hundreds of dollars on a dedicated oven), you can definitely do it with the oven you already have in your kitchen. With a few gadgets, you can improve your game without splurging on a Breville, Ooni or Solo Stove. First, I&#39;d recommend a high quality baking steel or stone.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAYhn2BEXBjIlUhVUE-gcCDCKkKEbWS800nVc0GwssboU&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FOld-Stone-Oven-Rectangular-Pizza%2Fdp%2FB0000E1FDA%3Fref_%3Dast_sto_dp">Baking stones</a> are great for getting better browning on the bottom of your pies than a pizza or sheet pan. You can also use them for bread, cookies and other items. The stone absorbs heat to cook pizza quickly, like the inside of a brick oven, which leads to a crisp crust. They&#39;re also more affordable compared to <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAeEbDEKojEDMsFXyWihRBYfzEgwmrp2Q1uKdD4J5W_F7&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBaking-Steel-Original-Ultra-Conductive%2Fdp%2FB00N205G22%3F">baking steels</a> . Those metal slabs do have one key advantage: higher heat conductivity. This means a steel will cook your pizzas faster since it can absorb more heat from your oven. While baking steels can be used as griddles on your stovetop and for other types of baking, they&#39;re not ideal for some leavened breads.</p><p> The second item you&#39;ll want is a <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9OZXctU3Rhci1Gb29kc2VydmljZS01MDI5NS1Xb29kZW4vZHAvQjAwOUxQRE5QTy8_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tc3AtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImU1ODJkZTQ3LTg1NTEtNDM4My1iZWE3LTExMjg5YjE0MzJlOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAeHLwzq7fJFIm1-ixj3_YAjMRj60G1dLxlCwHW3rnnFH&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FNew-Star-Foodservice-50295-Wooden%2Fdp%2FB009LPDNPO%2F">pizza peel</a> . These come in all shapes and sizes, made out of a variety of materials. I typically use a bamboo or wooden peel when topping and launching my pizzas and then a metal one for retrieving them. I&#39;ve found that dough doesn&#39;t stick as easily to bamboo during prep and the metal resists the high heat of the oven when turning or retrieving a finished pizza (bamboo will burn). There are also <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDdUNVMyTERELz90YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1zcC0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiZTU4MmRlNDctODU1MS00MzgzLWJlYTctMTEyODliMTQzMmU4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAdpQInLNp63_vvTnwW6Llpp877uFvnQmCfWr57mSHCYX&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB07T5S2LDD%2F">perforated peels</a> which allow both steam and excess flour to escape. A peel is a great tool for loading and turning pizzas, getting them in the back of the oven, and since you&#39;ll typically be cooking them with your oven at 500 degrees or hotter, using something like parchment paper to move them around won&#39;t work.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-pizza-oven-141550352.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-pizza-oven-141550352.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> e582de47-8551-4383-bea7-11289b1432e8</guid><dc:creator>比利斯蒂尔</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Thu, 08 Jun 2023 16:15:12 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686240914</ingested><modified> 2023-06-08T16:15:22+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Commodity Markets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Home & Garden]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Billy Steele]]></category><media:content height="1300" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-04/87fdc1d0-d9f6-11ed-a57f-bec0a4b17423" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:iden